* scan_memvar_parity_regression.dts
* Scan-path parity target — RED until the predx convergence lands, then GREEN.
*
* Proves a `$name` memory variable resolves in a FOR / scan predicate (the
* predx::eval_expr surface used by LOCATE / COUNT / SCAN / LIST FOR and SET FILTER),
* not only in the display path (?/CALC) and the IF/WHILE predicate path (AIF-041, done).
* The compiled scan/filter evaluator (predx) is the remaining path that does not yet
* resolve `$name` — and note `$` is ALSO the xBase substring-containment operator there,
* so the convergence hinges on the operand-leading `$name` detector, not just injection.
*
* Environment bootstrap (regression doctrine: every test sets its own environment; ambient
* default is STOP_ON_ERROR OFF): sets STOP_ON_ERROR OFF + ECHO OFF, and points the path
* slots at the SANDBOX area so the throwaway SCANREGR table never lands in live data.
*
* Pass criterion:
*   BEFORE convergence: SCAN_locate_predicate_memvar:FAIL-EXPECTED-UNTIL-CONVERGENCE
*   AFTER  convergence: SCAN_locate_predicate_memvar:PASS
*                       (LOCATE FOR VAL > $threshold lands on the first VAL > 15 = VAL 20)
*
* This test is intentionally NOT in the default suite until the convergence lands (it is
* RED, and it mutates the filesystem via CREATE/ERASE).
*
* Run:  REGRESSION RUN SCAN_PARITY
*   or: DOTSCRIPT dottalkpp/data/scripts/dotscript/scan_memvar_parity_regression.dts

SET ECHO OFF
STOP_ON_ERROR OFF
SET PATH DBF DBF/SANDBOX
SET PATH INDEXES INDEXES/SANDBOX
SET PATH LMDB LMDB/SANDBOX

FORMULA "SCAN-MEMVAR-PARITY-BEGIN"

* --- self-bootstrap a throwaway table: VAL = 10, 20, 30 (direct writes) ---
ERASE TABLE SCANREGR CONFIRM
CREATE X64 SCANREGR (ID N(4), VAL N(4))
APPEND
REPLACE ID WITH "1"
REPLACE VAL WITH "10"
APPEND
REPLACE ID WITH "2"
REPLACE VAL WITH "20"
APPEND
REPLACE ID WITH "3"
REPLACE VAL WITH "30"

* --- sanity: the memvar resolves in the DISPLAY path today (must be .T.) ---
VAR threshold = 15
? "SCAN_display_memvar_should_be_T:" + (($threshold + 5) = 20)

* --- target: LOCATE FOR is a FOR/scan predicate (predx); $threshold must resolve. ---
* GO TOP first so a RED no-op leaves the cursor on recno 1 (VAL=10) -> FAIL-EXPECTED.
GO TOP
LOCATE FOR VAL > $threshold
IF (VAL = 20)
  FORMULA "SCAN_locate_predicate_memvar:PASS"
ELSE
  FORMULA "SCAN_locate_predicate_memvar:FAIL-EXPECTED-UNTIL-CONVERGENCE"
ENDIF

* --- secondary (visible, not asserted): COUNT the same predicate; expect 2 after convergence ---
? "SCAN_count_expect_2_after_convergence:"
COUNT FOR VAL > $threshold

* --- cleanup ---
TABLE BUFFER OFF
CLOSE
ERASE TABLE SCANREGR CONFIRM

FORMULA "SCAN-MEMVAR-PARITY-END"
